==English==
===Noun===
'''space cadet'''

# {{slang}} term for someone who deals with [[reality]] in a way consistent with being under the influence of (or "spaced out on") drugs. The term may also be used in jest for someone who forgets, [[daydream]]s, or otherwise is distracted from reality more often than most. Another meaning popular in British English is taken from the word space meaning "empty" indicating that someone referred to as a space cadet is lacking in the grey matter department or to put it plainly, "has an empty head". It is thought that the use of the word cadet comes from the United Kingdom's Combined Cadet Force which is a military type boy scout organization for young adults of 13 to 18 years of age. Consisting of the 3 seperate cadet forces, the Army Cadet Force, the Navy Cadet Force and the Air Force Cadets. The use of the word space cadet implies that the person is so far detached from reality that they are more than suitable to join the fourth and non-existant cadre, the "Space Cadets".